@node Introduction

2. Introduction
₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤
TMouse is a small utility with common features such as mouse
accelerator and screen/pointer blanker.

TMouse can be started from Workbench, but it is recommend to
start TMouse from the Shell (i.e. S:Startup-Sequence). It
will detach itself from the Shell. To quit TMouse, run it a
second time.

TMouse will search for its configuration files TMouse.init,
TMouse.fkey and TMouse.menu in the S:-drawer. Copy these
files to S: and edit them with a text editor. TMouse will
automatically reload them whenever they are saved when
running under AmigaOS 2.0+.

TMouse is not a commodity, it uses input.device directly. It
doesn't use any functions within the handler that can lock
the system. TMouse doesn't patch any system functions.

TMouse works on AmigaOS 1.2 and higher. TMouse is freeware.


@endnode
@node TMouse.init

3. TMouse.init
₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤
This is TMouse's main configuration file. The options are
explained below. Any option can be commented out with ";",
and most are disabled with the value 0/NO/FALSE. N means any
number. OS 2.0+/3.0+ means that the option only has effect
on that and higher versions of AmigaOS.

ñ HandlerPri = 51 - 127
Priority of TMouse's handler (default 51).

ñ TMousePri = -128 - 19
Priority that TMouse will run at (default 4).

ñ Acceleration = n
Mouse acceleration.

ñ Threshold = n
Mouse acceleration threshold.

ñ MouseTime = n
Time in seconds before the mouse blanks.

ñ ScreenTime = n
Time in seconds before the screen blanks.

ñ AlertTime = n (OS 3.0+)
Maximum time in seconds that a system alert will be shown.

ñ ClickToFront = n
Number of clicks to pop window to front.

ñ VectorTime = n
Time in seconds between each check of vectors. TMouse will
warn you if ChkBase, ChkSum or KickCheckSum are invalid, and
whenever ColdCapture, CoolCapture, WarmCapture, KickTagPtr,
or KickMemPtr changes.

ñ VectorsOk = 0/1
TMouse will not warn you if any of the vectors are non-zero
when TMouse starts (ColdCapture, CoolCapture, WarmCapture,
KickTagPtr, KickMemPtr).

ñ AutoPoint = 0/1
Activates window under mouse pointer.

ñ ClickToBack = 0/1
Press right mouse button while holding the left to push
window to back.

ñ ScreenToBack = 0/1
Push screen to back if no window for ClickToBack.

ñ NoCapsLock = 0/1
Renders the caps lock key ineffective.

ñ Shanghai = 0/1 (OS 2.0+)
Workbench windows opens on default public screen.

ñ PopPubScreen = 0/1 (OS 2.0+)
When a window opens on a public screen, the screen will be
brought to the front.

ñ BlankBorder = 0/1 (OS 3.0+)
Makes the screen borders blank.

ñ WildStar = 0/1 (OS 2.0+)
Makes DOS handle "*" as "#?".

ñ NoClickDFX = 0/1 (OS 2.0+)
Makes floppy drive X stop making the click sound.


@endnode
@node TMouse.fkey

4. TMouse.fkey
₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤
This file defines hotkeys that TMouse will listen to and act
upon when pressed.

To define a new hotkey, enter its hexadecimal key code on a
new line (see "Hot Key" below). After this, enter one of the
commands listed below. If the command has an asterisk (*),
enter parameters for the command on new lines.

Below is a list of the commands together with a short
description of them:

ñ Cycle Windows          Cycle through windows.
ñ Cycle Screens          Cycle through screens.
ñ Enlarge Window         Make active window bigger.
ñ Shrink Window          Make active window smaller.
ñ Toggle Window Size     Change window size.
ñ Insert Text        (*) Insert text.
ñ Run Program        (*) Run program.
ñ Run ARexx Script   (*) Run ARexx script.
ñ Blanker                Start screen blanker.
ñ Screen Up              Move screens up one pixel.
ñ Screen Down            Move screens down one pixel.
ñ Screen Right           Move screens right one pixel.
ñ Screen Left            Move screens left one pixel.
ñ Lock X                 Lock mouse pointer in x-direction.
ñ Lock Y                 Lock mouse pointer in y-direction.
ñ Reboot                 Reboot the computer.
ñ Reboot Kill            Reboot computer and clear vectors.
ñ Toggle Workbench       Open or close the Workbench screen.
ñ Workbench To Front     Bring Workbench screen to front.
ñ Quit                   Quit TMouse.

ñ Execute Command    (*)
Works like the Execute Command in the Workbench menu. It
opens a requester where you can enter and execute a command
and its arguments.

ñ Hot Key
Open TMouse's window. When its activated and you press a key
combination (hotkey), it shows the hexadecimal key code for
the hotkey, to be used in this file to define new hotkeys.

ñ Reload
Reload TMouse's configuration files. Under OS 2.0+, TMouse
will use file notification and reload them automatically.


@endnode
@node TMouse.menu

5. TMouse.menu
₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤
TMouse will use this file when adding items to the Tools
menu in Workbench 2.0+.

What follows after a dollar sign ($) in this file will be
shown in the menu. The following lines (until the next
dollar sign ($) or end of file) will be executed when the
menu item is selected.

Each command will run asynchronously, with a stack size of
4096 bytes. The path and current directory will be the same
as TMouse's. You can change the stack size, path and current
directory with the DOS commands (i.e. Stack, Path and CD).


@endnode
@node Commands

6. Commands
₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤
I have included some CLI commands that can be useful
together with TMouse:

Delay (TIMEOUT/N)
Waits a specified period of time. 50 as argument waits 1
second.

PubScreen (PUBNAME/A,DEPTH/N) (OS 2.0+)
Opens a public screen with specified name and depth. You
can press Ctrl-C to close the screen and terminate
PubScreen. If someone opens a window on the screen,
PubScreen will automatically close the screen and quit
as soon as the window is closed.

WBToFront
Brings the Workbench screen to the front.


@endnode
